# Page theme infrastructure

The demo app uses a **token-first page theme system**. Every page surface
(colours, borders, shadows, status states, typography) flows through
`--page-*` custom properties — never hard-coded hex/rgb in HTML, TS, or
component markup.

## Source of truth

| Layer | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `demo/themes/page-theme-tokens.ts` | Theme ids, parody names, metadata, apply/resolve helpers |
| `demo/themes/page-themes.css` | **All colour values** — one `[data-page-theme='…']` block per theme |
| `demo/themes/page-theme-transitions.css` | `@property` registration + crossfade when theme changes |
| `demo/themes/page-theme-controller.ts` | Picker wiring, `localStorage`, `data-page-theme` on `<html>` |
| `demo/demo.css` | Layout/structure only — **must** reference `--page-*`, not literals |

Component Shadow DOM (`src/styles.ts`) may **fall back** to page tokens for
un-themed cards:

```css
--fc-fg: var(--page-fg, light-dark(…));
```

Per-card `data-theme` / `theme` attributes still override card accents.

## Required `--page-*` tokens (every theme block)

Every `[data-page-theme]` block in `page-themes.css` **must** define the
full set:

- `--page-bg`, `--page-bg-accent`
- `--page-fg`, `--page-muted`, `--page-accent`, `--page-on-accent`
- `--page-card`, `--page-border`, `--page-shadow`
- `--page-success`, `--page-success-border`
- `--page-warning`, `--page-warning-border`
- `--page-error`, `--page-error-border`
- `--page-font`
- `color-scheme: light | dark`

Use semantic status tokens for pills, validation output, and alerts —
**not** inline `light-dark()` per component.

## Adding a new theme

1. Add a `PageThemeId` + `PAGE_THEMES` entry in `page-theme-tokens.ts`
   (parody name required — even “normal” light/dark get joke names).
2. Add a complete token block in `page-themes.css`.
3. Options appear via `page-theme-controller.ts` (dynamic from registry).
4. Do **not** add colours anywhere else.

## Adding new demo UI

When creating sections, controls, or chrome:

1. Style with existing `--page-*` tokens only.
2. If a new semantic role is needed (e.g. `--page-info`), add it to **every**
   theme block in `page-themes.css` first, document it here, then use it in
   `demo.css`.
3. Never use `light-dark()` in `demo.css` — themes own light vs dark.
4. Never set `background`, `color`, or `border-color` literals on demo classes.

## Theme activation

- `<html data-page-theme="…">` set by `applyPageTheme()` / inline FOUC guard.
- Persisted under `fc-page-theme` in `localStorage`.
- System default: `corporate-daydream` (light) / `pager-duty-noir` (dark).

## Do not

- Bypass the registry with one-off `<style>` blocks or inline styles.
- Put page theme colours in `demo/main.ts` (TS handles ids only, not colours).
- Style shadow internals from the demo — page tokens cascade via `:host` fallbacks only.
